Paper: hep-th/9807057

Date: 1998-07-08

Title: Enhanced gauge symmetries on elliptic K3

Authors: L.Bonora, C.Reina, A.Zampa

Comments: 9 pages, Latex

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B452 (1999) 244-250

We show that the geometry of K3 surfaces with singularities of type A-D-Econtains enough information to reconstruct a copy of the Lie algebra associatedto the given Dynkin diagram. We apply this construction to explain theenhancement of symmetry in F and IIA theories compactified on singular K3's.